<p>For one of my class methods to create a new window and print an AVL tree, I've been try to fit an AVL Tree into the window. When my AVL Tree gets too big, some parts of the tree will not be able to be shown within the window and will be cut off at the window's borders.</p>  <p>I've tried using the below code with BorderLayout centering, but to no avail. How can I make sure that the AVL Tree appears inside the window and resizes accordingly?</p>  <p>Either that, or how can I make the window scrollable so the person can see the parts of the tree that is outside the window coz it is too big?</p>  <pre><code>    public static &lt;K, V&gt; void print(AVLTree&lt;K, V&gt; tree) {     Dimension screenSize = Toolkit.getDefaultToolkit().getScreenSize();     int x = (int)screenSize.getWidth();     int y = (int)screenSize.getHeight();      JFrame j = new JFrame();     j.setLayout(new BorderLayout()); // centering     j.add(new TreeDiagram&lt;K, V&gt;(tree), BorderLayout.CENTER);     j.pack(); // resize window to fit size and layout of sub components     j.setResizable(false); // user cannot resize window     j.setTitle("AVLTree");     j.setSize(x, y);     j.setLocationRelativeTo(null);     j.setLocationByPlatform(true);     j.setDefaultCloseOperation(JFrame.EXIT_ON_CLOSE);     j.setVisible(true); } </code></pre>